sentences: Arun Thapa Magar(Nepali:अरुण थापा)  (born January 1952 – 22 July 1999) was a Nepali singer and songwriter.

In 2003, according to an international poll conducted by BBC, more than half-a million people from 165 countries voted his composition Reetu haruma timi hariyali basant (You are the spring amongst the seasons), his most famous romantic song, as the seventh in the world's top 10 most popular songs of all time.
Later he studied in Turnbull High school in Darjeeling, coming back to complete his School Leaving Certificate (SLC) from Kathmandu in 1971.
He first sang his song in Radio Nepal in 1971.
He died on 22 July 1999 (BS 2056 Shravan 5 at 1815 hrs) in Kathmandu.
